In this context, the term "open the input" is a term used in computer programming. The person talking is referring to the action of opening the data file (here, 'Tiny Shakespeare') to read its contents. Opening data files is a common step in data analysis and machine learning projects. In this example, they will read this data file in order to train a Transformer-based language model. "Opening the input" is about preparing to process the initial raw data, which will be used to create and train the AI model.